25 Jun 2017 19:36






I still have a bunch of issues with the article. (my silly opinion)

1. The article is not thematically in line with the Foundation. There is too much emphasis on the suffering and misery of the SCP, how she's suicidal and all that jazz, and very little emphasis on the anomalous properties. Unless her anomalous property is that she's constantly miserable and depressed.

2. The SCP has next to no personality. Even with interview logs and stuff, there isn't much to her other than , which IMO, is not realistic. Even when people are severely depressed, they still retain at least a few of their individual personality quirks.

3. My biggest gripe: the SCP is too melodramatic to be realistic. There's too much emphasis on her torment and too many terrible things happen to her without rhyme or reason. All in all it feels more like a clumsy attempt at  rather than a genuine tragedy. I can't feel sorry for her because the sheer misfortune she has gone through is just too over-the-top and it destroys my suspension of disbelief.

Down boat for now.





